cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The use of compression techniques and joint decoding suggests a possible categorization under cs.MM (Multimedia), while the consideration of state-dependent channels and feedback mechanisms may lead to a categorization under cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the use of theoretical analysis and capacity results may suggest a categorization under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
